headline: Visa Expands Beyond Cards With Crypto Off Ramps And Rent Payments
summary: Visa (NYSE:V) has partnered with Mercuryo to support global crypto to fiat conversions through Visa cards and accounts. The company is also working with Amenify to integrate payments and resident commerce for renters. These agreements highlight Visa's recent push into digital assets, embedded finance and lifestyle focused payment solutions. Visa, known primarily for its global card network, is leaning further into digital commerce infrastructure that sits behind everyday transactions. The...

headline: 10 Fidelity ETFs With The Lowest Expense Ratio For Retirees

headline: How To Earn $500 A Month From Visa Stock Ahead Of Q1 Earnings
summary: Visa Inc. (NYSE:V) will release earnings for its first quarter after the closing bell on Thursday, Jan. 29. Analysts expect the company to report quarterly earnings of $3.14 per share. That’s up from $2.75 per share in the year-ago period. The consensus estimate for Visa's quarterly revenue is $10.69 billion (it reported $9.51 billion last year), according to Benzinga Pro.
